  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'=
>Large
  nebulae clouds can be found throughout the galaxy. They cover vast areas =
of
  space with a hazy fog of gas and dust. Nebulae are usually the dispersed
  remnants of supernovas &#8211; exploded stars.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'=
>Nebulae
  clouds can affect your ships in various ways. These effects can include:<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
  mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'><span style=3D'mso-l=
ist:
  Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><=
span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Movement slowed:</span></b=
><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'> all nebulae clouds slow t=
he
  movement of ships when not in hyperspace<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-lis=
t:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
  mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'><span style=3D'mso-l=
ist:
  Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><=
span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Shields reduced:</span></b=
><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'> some nebulae drain the en=
ergy
  from ship&#8217;s shields<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-lis=
t:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
  mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'><span style=3D'mso-l=
ist:
  Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><=
span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Hyperjump disabled:</span>=
</b><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'> some clouds prevent hyper=
drives
  from working. Inside these clouds you cannot initiate a hyperjump. Instead
  you must first slowly travel to the edge of the cloud using conventional
  engines before your hyperdrive resumes functioning<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:=
l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
  mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'><span style=3D'mso-l=
ist:
  Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><=
span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Storm damage:</span></b><s=
pan
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'> some nebulae clouds conta=
in
  violent ion storms that can damage ships and bases<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'=
>Nebulae
  clouds also have the effect of shaping the galaxy. This is because stars
  rarely form inside nebulae clouds. Instead stars tend to cluster between
  clouds. This can leave large voids of space between star clusters, formin=
g a
  natural &#8220;geography&#8221; to the galaxy</span>. On the other hand G=
as
  clouds will only form inside Nebulae.</p>
